reviewText: very good workout and it is only about 30 minutes, so if you are in a crunch for time, you can always squeeze it in.  mostly lower body stuff.
Title: Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs

reviewText: I love turbo jam in general so it wasn't surprise that I'd fall in love with this one also. It's live so Chalene is a bit more outgoing and fun (she's always fun but she was really fun on this one lol)  It's not a long workout (only 30 minutes) but it gets the job done. You break a sweat and it gets the heart pumping. My favorite part is with the resistance band you can really feel the burn. (The Resistance Band and Free Weights are Optional but they are GREAT to use.) The ab part will not be difficult to anyone who's used to doing "Ab Jam" I had no trouble. I felt the burn but it wasn't agonizing. The weight training was good. One thing I will say is that this really isn't an "alternative" to "Turbo Sculpt" by any means. Turbo Sculpt is a much more intense workout but with that being said this one is a total body workout just not as much as turbo scuplt. I love it. And it's definitely added into my turbo jam workouts weekly. I combine it withTURBO JAM FAT BLASTERanother must have.
Title: Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs

reviewText: I love this DVD. It came yesterday and I couldn't be happier. I was unsure if this was a total body workout or not and it is.  The DVD includes light weights and an exercise band workout but can be done without them.There are two girls in the DVD that show a less intense and more intense workout than what Chalene is doing. The routine was shot during one of her classes and is easy to follow for a live routine.There is also a bar on the bottom of the screen that tells how much longer the routine is.  It is very helpful. However, with Chalene the workouts seem to breeze by and I hardly even looked at the bar.I highly recommend this DVD.
summary: This is a total body workout
Title: Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs

reviewText: I own just about all of these Turbo Jam videos and I love them.  This one is especially good when I don't have 40-60 minutes to devote to my workout.  It covers cardio, weights, and abs.  I would recommend this workout to anyone who has tried the Turbo Jam videos.  Great product!
Title: Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs

reviewText: I've been working out at home for just about eight years now but only recently discovered Chalene Johnson and her Turbo Jam series. Where have you been all my life, Chalene! I have never enjoyed (really enjoyed, not just tolerated) working out as much as I do with Turbo Jam."Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs" is a 30-minute total body strength workout with that signature Turbo Jam "gotta shake it" soundtrack. For me, the pace is just fast enough to work up a nice sweat but not so fast that it compromises good form. Chalene hits all the standard muscles here, biceps, triceps, shoulders, inner and outer thigh, glutes, and abs. No chest, so push-up lovers might be disappointed (but push-up loathers, like me, get a break).The best thing about Turbo Jam is that when I'm done, I feel great. It's a challenging workout that, for me, pushes me just up to my limit but not past it into complete exhaustion. There is no dread factor, which makes maintaining a workout schedule a whole lot easier.
Title: Turbo Jam Live! Booty Sculpt + Abs
